george cables trio and madeline eastman events at stanford george cables trio and madeline eastman facebook twitter email print add to calendar individually vocalist madeline eastman and pianist george cables have achieved just about all there is to achieve in jazz they ve toured the world performed and recorded with the greats and won accolades and admiration from the press and the people alike what happens when they re together only you will know at this special closing evening of the stanford jazz festival you ll get to hear what happens when these two towering talents these most sensitive of artists spontaneously create music together bassist larry grenadier and drummer gregory hutchinson longtime sjw faculty and world class artists themselves are joined by special guest trumpeter marcus belgrave to support madeline and george of madeline stereophile magazine says she's hitting from beginning to end sizzling and snapping with electricity sliding across bar lines scatting choruses slowing to a whisper bending melody line to her will she is in charge when saturday august 6 2011 8 00 pm approximate duration of 2 hour s where campbell recital hall 541 lasuen mall stanford ca 94305 map audience faculty staff alumni friends general public students members tags performance music arts sponsor stanford jazz workshop contact 736 0324 info stanfordjazz org admission tickets $36 general $22 students stanford ticket office 650 725 arts 2787 http tickets stanford edu permalink http events stanford edu events 280 28005 more info last modified august 1 2011
